                            <comment id="13603353" author="rhillegas" created="Fri, 15 Mar 2013 13:16:21 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi Myrna,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Can you give more information about this problem? The release script updates release.properties twice:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;1) At the beginning, the script prompts for the new release id. This is written to release.properties.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;2) At the end, the script bumps the last digit of the release id in release.properties.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Did the release manager give a correct release id in step (1) but the script somehow corrupted it? Or did the script faithfully do what the release manager directed? Thanks.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13625902" author="myrna" created="Mon, 8 Apr 2013 23:16:26 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi Rick, I somehow missed that you were asking this question.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It&apos;s been a while since I did this, but if you look at the release.properties file on the 10.8 branch, drdmaint is (currently) 1.&lt;br/&gt;
After running ant release for that branch, it was set to 0. &lt;br/&gt;
It did not prompt for drdamaint number. &lt;br/&gt;
That&apos;s different from the release id!&lt;br/&gt;
Perhaps it should figure out what it is in release.properties before starting, and unless it gets modified, drdamaint should be unchanged.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We can look at this some more later - for 10.9 and 10.10 and trunk drdamaint is 0, so it doesn&apos;t matter right now.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13869687" author="knutanders" created="Mon, 13 Jan 2014 16:57:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This bug seems to have bitten us again. The DRDA maintenance version was reset to 0 on the 10.8 branch in revision 1557213, which makes derbynet.PrepareStatementTest.testLongColumn fail: &lt;a href=&quot;http://download.java.net/javadesktop/derby/request_5586103/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://download.java.net/javadesktop/derby/request_5586103/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13869876" author="rhillegas" created="Mon, 13 Jan 2014 19:40:55 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Attaching derby-5463-01-aa-leaveDRDAmaintIDAlone.diff. This patch makes the ReleaseProperties program read release.properties, fetch the current value of drdamaint, and then write that value out when it regenerates the file.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
